The three MAbs reacted with the receptor-binding domain (RBD) of the MERS-CoV S protein but not the RBD of S proteins from other coronaviruses, namely, SARS-CoV (Fig. 1
A), Bt-CoV-HKU4, and Bt-CoV-HKU5 (Fig. 1B). The isotype of the 45E11 and 45C2 MAbs was IgG1/kappa while the 43A9 isotype was IgG2a/kappa. In the plaque reduction assay, the concentrations of 45E11, 45C2, and 43A9 that inhibited MERS-CoV infection by 50% were 0.1, 0.25, and 1.94 μg/mL, respectively (Fig. 2
).
